{"title_page": "V. P. Singh Badnore", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Vijayender Pal Singh Badnore\n| image = V P Singh Badnore.JPG\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1948|5|12|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Badnor, Rajasthan|Badnor]], [[Rajputana]], [[Dominion of India|India]]\n| residence = [[Bhilwara]], [[Rajasthan]] (private)<br />[[Raj Bhavan (Punjab)|Raj Bhavan]], [[Chandigarh]] (official)\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| office = [[List of governors of Punjab (India)|28th Governor of Punjab]]\n| term_start = 22 August 2016 <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/najma-heptulla-mukhi-appointed-governors-116081700886_1.html|title=Najma Heptulla, Mukhi appointed Governors|publisher=Business Standard|date=17 August 2016|newspaper=Business Standard India}}</ref>\n| term_end = \n| constituency = \n| 1blankname = Chief Minister\n| 1namedata = [[Prakash Singh Badal]]<br>[[Amarinder Singh]]\n| predecessor = [[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]\n| successor = \n| office1 = 14th [[Administrator of Chandigarh]]\n| term_start1 = 22 August 2016\n| term_end1 = \n| predecessor1 = [[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]\n| office2 = [[Lok Sabha|Member of Parliament (Lok Sabha)]]\n| term_start2 = 1999\n| term_end2 = 2009\n| constituency2 = [[Bhilwara (Lok Sabha constituency)|Bhilwara]]\n| predecessor2 = Rampal Upadhyay\n| successor2 = [[C. P. Joshi]]\n| office3 = [[Member of Parliament (India)|Member of Parliament]]  ([[Rajya Sabha]])\n| term_start3 = 5 July 2010\n| term_end3 = 4 July 2016\n| constituency3 = [[Rajasthan]]\n| predecessor3 = \n| successor3 = \n| party = [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]]\n| religion = \n| spouse = {{Marriage|Alka Singh|1978}}\n| children = 2\n| website = \n| footnotes = \n| date = 14 September|\n| year = 2006|\n| source = https://web.archive.org/web/20071107073404/http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=30\n| president = [[Ramnath Kovind]]\n}}\n\n'''Vijayender Pal Singh Badnore''' (born 12 May 1948) is an Indian politician serving as the 28th and current [[List of Governors of Punjab (India)|Governor of Punjab]]. He was a member of [[Rajya Sabha]], elected on 17 June 2010. He was earlier a member of the [[14th Lok Sabha]] and [[13th Lok Sabha]] of the [[Indian Parliament]]. He represented the [[Bhilwara (Lok Sabha Constituency)|Bhilwara]] constituency of [[Rajasthan]] and is a member of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP) political party from 1999\u20132009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/who-is-vp-singh-badnore-5-things-to-know-about-the-new-punjab-governor/story-BPF69z9W1qEqebkIFvckfL.html|title=Who is VP Singh Badnore? 5 things to know about the new Punjab governor|date=17 August 2016|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSingh was born in [[Badnor, Rajasthan|Badnor]], [[Rajasthan]] to Gopal Singh and Raj Kanwar Nathawad. He completed is schooling from [[Mayo College]] in [[Ajmer]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{cite web |title=Current Lok Sabha Members Biographical Sketch |url=http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=30 |accessdate=20 July 2019 |date=7 November 2007|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071107073404/http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=30|archive-date = 7 November 2007}}</ref> Singh married Alka Singh on 25 November 1978. They have a son and a daughter.<ref name=\"Bio\"/>\n\n==As Punjab Governor==\nHe was appointed as Governor of Punjab on 17 August 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/chandigarh/punjab-gets-new-governor-2982193/|title=VP Singh Badnore appointed Punjab Governor|publisher=The Indian Express|date=18 August 2016 |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Other participation ==\n{{citation needed section|date=July 2019}}\n# Initial experience in the Corporate World. Management Cadre in Escorts Ltd. 1970\u20131977. \n# Sr. Managers Business Management Course at ASCI Hyderabad (1974)\n#[[Rajasthan Legislative Assembly|Member of Rajasthan Legislative Assembly]] (1977\u201380, 1985\u201390, 1993\u201398, 1998-99)\n# Member, [[13th Lok Sabha|Thirteenth Lok Sabha]] (1999-2004)\n#Member, [[14th Lok Sabha|Fourteenth Lok Sabha]] (2004-2009) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabrajbhavan.gov.in/home/governor|title=The Present Governor|last=|first=|date=|website=Punjabrajbhavan.gov.in|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n# Member\u00a0 of\u00a0 [[Rajya Sabha]] (2010-2016)\n#Nominated to the Panel of Vice Chairman, Rajya Sabha in August 2014 \n#Cabinet Minister in [[Bhairon Singh Shekhawat|Bhairon Singh]] ji BJP Government in [[Rajasthan]] (Irrigation Department)\n# Vice President in BJP Sangathan Raj. for over 15 years.\n# Special interest in Energy (Power sector). Member of standing committee of Parliament for last 14 years. Convener of the Drafting committee of the Electricity Act 2003.\n# Member of the Governing body of Mayo College Ajmer for the last 25 years. Architect of the Mayo School branches (Mayoor School) in various places including Abu Dhabi UAE.\n# Chairman of the Tiger Task Force in Raj. After the Sariska debacle \u2013 when all tigers were poached in Sariska in 2003/2004. Rehabilitation of tigers done by translocation of tigers from Ranthambore Tiger Reserve. First time in the world such a Herculean task was carried out. Panna tiger reserve also followed suit and tigers were then rehabilitated there as well.\n# Attended senior parliamentary leadership program in the Yale University USA on their invitation in 2012.\n# Was in charge of Bhilwara & Dungarpur - Banswara tribal belt in the state and general elections 2013 \u2013 2014. In the state election of 2008 only 2 out of 17 seats came to BJP and lost both the MP seats, this time 14 out 17 MLA seats and both the MP seats were collected by the BJP.\n# Enjoy an impeccable record of Honesty, Hardwork and Loyalty towards the BJP and was therefore selected to the Rajya Sabha seat in 2010 from Rajasthan.\n# Was selected in the Times Of India survey of top 25 MPs\u2019 of Lok Sabha in the year 2003\u20132008.\n# Is the chief guest of 21st SLIET  Convocation ceremony.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/members/former_Biography.aspx?mpsno=30 Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n* [http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-06-18/jaipur/28297053_1_ashk-ali-tak-votes-bjp-share-honours ess, BJP share honours in RS polls]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|in-lwr}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rampal Upadhyay]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of Parliament<br>for [[Bhilwara (Lok Sabha constituency)|Bhilwara]]|years=1999 \u2013 2009}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[C. P. Joshi]]}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of governors of Punjab (India)|Governor of Punjab, India]]|years=22 August 2016 \u2013 Present}}\n{{s-aft|after=Incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Current Indian governors}}\n{{Rajya Sabha members from Rajasthan for term 2010-2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Badnore, Vijayendrapal Singh}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Mayo College alumni]]\n[[Category:13th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:14th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:People from Bhilwara district]]\n[[Category:Rajya Sabha members from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Rajasthan MLAs 1977\u20131980]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Vijayender Pal Singh Badnore\n| image = V P Singh Badnore.JPG\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1948|5|12|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Badnor, Rajasthan|Badnor]], [[Rajputana]], [[Dominion of India|India]]\n| residence = [[Bhilwara]], [[Rajasthan]] (private)<br />[[Raj Bhavan (Punjab)|Raj Bhavan]], [[Chandigarh]] (official)\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| office = [[List of governors of Punjab (India)|28th Governor of Punjab]]\n| term_start = 22 August 2016 <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/najma-heptulla-mukhi-appointed-governors-116081700886_1.html|title=Najma Heptulla, Mukhi appointed Governors|publisher=Business Standard|date=17 August 2016|newspaper=Business Standard India}}</ref>\n| term_end = \n| constituency = \n| 1blankname = Chief Minister\n| 1namedata = [[Prakash Singh Badal]]<br>[[Amarinder Singh]]\n| predecessor = [[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]\n| successor = \n| office1 = 14th [[Administrator of Chandigarh]]\n| term_start1 = 22 August 2016\n| term_end1 = \n| predecessor1 = [[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]\n| office2 = [[Lok Sabha|Member of Parliament (Lok Sabha)]]\n| term_start2 = 1999\n| term_end2 = 2009\n| constituency2 = [[Bhilwara (Lok Sabha constituency)|Bhilwara]]\n| predecessor2 = Rampal Upadhyay\n| successor2 = [[C. P. Joshi]]\n| office3 = [[Member of Parliament (India)|Member of Parliament]]  ([[Rajya Sabha]])\n| term_start3 = 5 July 2010\n| term_end3 = 4 July 2016\n| constituency3 = [[Rajasthan]]\n| predecessor3 = \n| successor3 = \n| party = [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]]\n| religion = \n| spouse = {{Marriage|Alka Singh|1978}}\n| children = 2\n| website = \n| footnotes = \n| date = 14 September|\n| year = 2006|\n| source = https://web.archive.org/web/20071107073404/http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=30\n| president = [[Ramnath Kovind]]\n}}\n\n'''Vijayender Pal Singh Badnore''' (born 12 May 1948) is an Indian politician serving as the 28th and current [[List of Governors of Punjab (India)|Governor of Punjab]]. He was a member of [[Rajya Sabha]], elected on 17 June 2010. He was earlier a member of the [[14th Lok Sabha]] and [[13th Lok Sabha]] of the [[Indian Parliament]]. He represented the [[Bhilwara (Lok Sabha Constituency)|Bhilwara]] constituency of [[Rajasthan]] and is a member of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP) political party from 1999\u20132009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/who-is-vp-singh-badnore-5-things-to-know-about-the-new-punjab-governor/story-BPF69z9W1qEqebkIFvckfL.html|title=Who is VP Singh Badnore? 5 things to know about the new Punjab governor|date=17 August 2016|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSingh was born in [[Badnor, Rajasthan|Badnor]], [[Rajasthan]] to Gopal Singh and Raj Kanwar Nathawad. He completed his [[Bachelor of Arts]] (Honours) in English and Business Management from [[Mayo College]] in [[Ajmer]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{cite web |title=Current Lok Sabha Members Biographical Sketch |url=http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=30 |accessdate=20 July 2019 |date=7 November 2007|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071107073404/http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=30|archive-date = 7 November 2007}}</ref> Singh married Alka Singh on 25 November 1978. They have a son and a daughter.<ref name=\"Bio\"/>\n\n==As Punjab Governor==\nHe was appointed as Governor of Punjab on 17 August 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/chandigarh/punjab-gets-new-governor-2982193/|title=VP Singh Badnore appointed Punjab Governor|publisher=The Indian Express|date=18 August 2016 |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Other participation ==\n{{citation needed section|date=July 2019}}\n# Initial experience in the Corporate World. Management Cadre in Escorts Ltd. 1970\u20131977. \n# Sr. Managers Business Management Course at ASCI Hyderabad (1974)\n#[[Rajasthan Legislative Assembly|Member of Rajasthan Legislative Assembly]] (1977\u201380, 1985\u201390, 1993\u201398, 1998-99)\n# Member, [[13th Lok Sabha|Thirteenth Lok Sabha]] (1999-2004)\n#Member, [[14th Lok Sabha|Fourteenth Lok Sabha]] (2004-2009) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabrajbhavan.gov.in/home/governor|title=The Present Governor|last=|first=|date=|website=Punjabrajbhavan.gov.in|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n# Member\u00a0 of\u00a0 [[Rajya Sabha]] (2010-2016)\n#Nominated to the Panel of Vice Chairman, Rajya Sabha in August 2014 \n#Cabinet Minister in [[Bhairon Singh Shekhawat|Bhairon Singh]] ji BJP Government in [[Rajasthan]] (Irrigation Department)\n# Vice President in BJP Sangathan Raj. for over 15 years.\n# Special interest in Energy (Power sector). Member of standing committee of Parliament for last 14 years. Convener of the Drafting committee of the Electricity Act 2003.\n# Member of the Governing body of Mayo College Ajmer for the last 25 years. Architect of the Mayo School branches (Mayoor School) in various places including Abu Dhabi UAE.\n# Chairman of the Tiger Task Force in Raj. After the Sariska debacle \u2013 when all tigers were poached in Sariska in 2003/2004. Rehabilitation of tigers done by translocation of tigers from Ranthambore Tiger Reserve. First time in the world such a Herculean task was carried out. Panna tiger reserve also followed suit and tigers were then rehabilitated there as well.\n# Attended senior parliamentary leadership program in the Yale University USA on their invitation in 2012.\n# Was in charge of Bhilwara & Dungarpur - Banswara tribal belt in the state and general elections 2013 \u2013 2014. In the state election of 2008 only 2 out of 17 seats came to BJP and lost both the MP seats, this time 14 out 17 MLA seats and both the MP seats were collected by the BJP.\n# Enjoy an impeccable record of Honesty, Hardwork and Loyalty towards the BJP and was therefore selected to the Rajya Sabha seat in 2010 from Rajasthan.\n# Was selected in the Times Of India survey of top 25 MPs\u2019 of Lok Sabha in the year 2003\u20132008.\n# Is the chief guest of 21st SLIET  Convocation ceremony.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/members/former_Biography.aspx?mpsno=30 Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n* [http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-06-18/jaipur/28297053_1_ashk-ali-tak-votes-bjp-share-honours ess, BJP share honours in RS polls]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|in-lwr}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rampal Upadhyay]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of Parliament<br>for [[Bhilwara (Lok Sabha constituency)|Bhilwara]]|years=1999 \u2013 2009}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[C. P. Joshi]]}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of governors of Punjab (India)|Governor of Punjab, India]]|years=22 August 2016 \u2013 Present}}\n{{s-aft|after=Incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Current Indian governors}}\n{{Rajya Sabha members from Rajasthan for term 2010-2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Badnore, Vijayendrapal Singh}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Mayo College alumni]]\n[[Category:13th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:14th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:People from Bhilwara district]]\n[[Category:Rajya Sabha members from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Rajasthan MLAs 1977\u20131980]]\n", "name_user": "DigvijaySingh1", "label": "safe", "comment": "Earlier it mentioned that Mr Singh completed his Bachelor of Arts (Honours) in English and Business Management from Mayo College, but in reality, Mayo College is a private residential school and not a college. Hence Mr Singh completed his schooling from Mayo and not his undergraduate degree.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V._P._Singh_Badnore"}
