=\nOn 13 December 2019, Pink Floyd released the box set, ''[[The Later Years 1987\u20132019]]''. The box contains a 5.1 surround mix of ''The Endless River'' set to a film by [[Ian Emes]]; artwork related to the album; and previously unreleased tracks from ''The Division Bell'' sessions, including \"Nervana\". Also included are the \"Louder than Words\" video, a video of the album's launch party, and the [[electronic press kit]].\n\n==Personnel==\nAdapted from the 2014 release<ref>liner notes to the 2014 release</ref>\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Pink Floyd'''\n*[[David Gilmour]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[guitar#Electric guitars|guitars]] {{small|(all but 3)}}, [[EBow]] guitar {{small|(1, 3, 10)}}, [[lead vocalist|lead vocals]] {{small|(18)}}, [[backing vocalist|backing vocals]] {{small|(7, 14, 17)}}, [[keyboard instrument|keyboards]] {{small|(7, 15, 16)}}, [[piano]] {{small|(6, 7)}}, [[EMS VCS 3]] {{small|(4, 6)}}, [[bass guitar]] {{small|(2, 4, 7, 17)}}, [[Hammond organ]] {{small|(18)}}, [[percussion instrument|percussion]] {{small|(8)}}, [[Sampling (music)|voice samples]] {{small|(1)}}, [[record producer|producer]]\n*[[Nick Mason]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Drum kit|drums]] {{small|(2, 4, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 14, 16, 17, 18)}}, percussion {{small|(15, 18)}}, [[rototom]]s {{small|(5)}}, [[gong]] {{small|(5, 12, 16)}}, voice samples {{small|(1)}}\n*[[Richard Wright (musician)|Richard Wright]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Hammond organ]] {{small|(1, 11, 13, 16)}}, [[Farfisa|Farfisa organ]] {{small|(4, 6, 14, 16)}}, [[Royal Albert Hall Organ]] {{small|(12)}}, piano {{small|(4, 6, 8, 14, 18)}}, [[Rhodes piano]] {{small|(9, 18)}}, electric piano {{small|(3)}}, keyboards {{small|(1, 2, 5, 16, 17)}}, [[synthesiser]] {{small|(1, 2, 8, 10, 14, 17, 18)}}, voice samples {{small|(1, 18)}}\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[Guy Pratt]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar {{small|(9, 14)}}\n*[[Bob Ezrin]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar {{small|(11, 13, 18)}}, additional keyboards {{small|(1)}}\n*[[Andy Jackson (recording engineer)|Andy Jackson]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar {{small|(5, 16)}}, effects {{small|(15)}}\n*[[Jon Carin]]&nbsp;\u2013 synthesisers {{small|(9, 11, 13)}}, percussion loop {{small|(11, 13)}}\n*Damon Iddins&nbsp;\u2013 additional keyboards {{small|(4, 12)}}\n*[[Anthony Moore]]&nbsp;\u2013 keyboards {{small|(15)}}\n*[[Gilad Atzmon]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[tenor saxophone]] {{small|(7)}}, [[clarinet]] {{small|(7)}}\n*[[Durga McBroom]]&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals {{small|(14, 17, 18)}}\n*Louise Marshal&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals {{small|(18)}}\n*Sarah Brown&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals {{small|(18)}}\n*[[Stephen Hawking]]&nbsp;\u2013 voice sample {{small|(14)}}\n*[[Martin Glover|Youth]]&nbsp;\u2013 additional programming, engineering, sound design, assorted synthesisers and keyboards\n*Eddie Bander&nbsp;\u2013 additional programming, engineering, sound design, assorted synthesisers and keyboards\n*Michael Rendall&nbsp;\u2013 additional programming, engineering, sound design, assorted synthesisers and keyboards\n* [[Escala (group)|Escala]]:\n** Chantal Leverton&nbsp;\u2013 [[viola]] {{small|(18)}}\n** Victoria Lyon&nbsp;\u2013 [[violin]] {{small|(18)}}\n** Helen Nash&nbsp;\u2013 [[cello]] {{small|(18)}}\n** Honor Watson&nbsp;\u2013 violin {{small|(18)}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Production and design'''\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[Phil Manzanera]]&nbsp;\u2013 producer\n*[[Martin Glover|Youth]]&nbsp;\u2013 producer\n*[[Andrew Jackson (recording engineer)|Andy Jackson]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[audio engineer|engineer]], producer, mixing, mastering of bonus content on DVD and Blu-ray\n*[[Bob Ezrin]]&nbsp;\u2013 co-producer 1993 sessions\n*Damon Iddins&nbsp;\u2013 [[audio engineer|engineer]]\n*[[James Guthrie (record producer)|James Guthrie]]&nbsp;\u2013 mastering for CD<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soundbard.com/soundbard/louder-than-words-producer-andy-jackson-takes-us-exclusively-inside-the-making-of-the-final-pink-floyd-album-the-endless-river/ |title=Louder Than Words: Producer 